result.execSummary:
The defendant Caitlyn M Lautenbach was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Caitlyn M Lautenbach is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Caitlyn M Lautenbach was found guilty of Operate with Restricted Controlled Substance (2nd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(am).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Caitlyn M Lautenbach in court with attorney Joan B Broughton.  Debra Lynn Blasius appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 3.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 1 dismissed and read in.  Count 2 dismissed by operation of law.

Court orders the following: 
- 6 months Huber with standard release conditions. STAYED
- 1 year Probation
- 16 months Drivers License Revocation. 
- 16 months Ignition Interlock on any vehicle TITLED OR REGISTERED to defendant 
- Alcohol Assessment
- Fine of $1,179.00; cash bail to be applied.  Any remaining fine to be paid as a Condition of Probation
- Blood Test Reimbursement of $24.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forwarded to Brookfield Police Department
- DNA Surcharge waived
- Conditions of Probation:  Maintain absolute sobriety/Random UAs.  No use or possession of alcohol/drug paraphernalia/drugs without a valid prescription.  Submit to a Mental Health assessment and follow through with any treatment/counseling.  Maintain full-time employment and/or school.
